	standing of how fentanyl and opioid use disorders intersect with mental he
	alth conditions and contribute to homelessness in the Seattle-King County 
	region.Learn how integrated behavioral health care addressing both substan
	ce use disorder and mental illness leads to improved recovery outcomes and
	 community stability.Explore the direct and indirect impacts of behavioral
	 health challenges on employers\, workforce participation\, and regional e
	conomic health.Identify opportunities for collaboration between businesses
	\, nonprofits\, healthcare providers\, and public-sector partners to expan
	d access to care\, reduce stigma\, and strengthen prevention and recovery 
	networks.
