	nth
DTSTAMP:20260214T003548Z
DTSTART:20260219T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of Black History Month 2026\, the City of Bellev
	ue is working with community partners to present "Melodies of the Diaspora
	: Celebrating 100 Years of Black History Month\," an art exhibition featur
	ing the work of Pacific Northwest Black artists on display at the Bellevue
	 Arts Museum and Bellevue City Hall and is designed to take visitors on a 
	chronological journey of Black art through downtown Bellevue.\n\nThe exhib
	ition will feature paintings\, photography\, sculptures\, textiles and fas
	hion and is curated by Jay Taylor\, Fancy Vargas and Jerry Lee.
